author: @morphman86
text: Thanks for the great tutorials. Just as a note though, I couldn't bother to type in the address to your test page, or even check if it still exists, so I just copied the link to this video. One of the URL's found, one of the very last ones, looked interesting: /testtube  Checked it out, and you can only access it through code, knowing the link and putting it in directly or somehow managing to get to the bottom of a video page before you're overloaded by comments. Right at the bottom, before the Copyright information, there's a tiny link to "Test new features", leading to the TestTube.  Apparently it's been around for a few years, but I've never heard of it before... and I'm actively looking for news about technology, coding and Youtube (as I'm a tech writer for an entertainment magazine). If I didn't know about it, I'm willing to bet most others didn't either.  The things you find when you go looking in places most people don't see.
